<paragraph blockId="10.[143,369,1563,1626]" box="[143,369,1602,1626]" pageId="10" pageNumber="1266">BL: 10.61, BW: 2.19</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[143,857,1666,1690]" lastBlockId="11.[211,1172,167,510]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="1267" pageId="10" pageNumber="1266">
Body strongly depressed. Body all black except tarsi red-brown. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,279,167,191]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Head.</emphasis>
Transverse (
<figureCitation box="[420,537,167,191]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
). Inner lateral teeth separated by a depression extending to base. Inner and outer lateral teeth fused and resembling a septum; median sulcus deep, sides of median sulcus parallel; laterofrontal depressions oval. Labrum with outer edge strongly angled and lateral-apical edge concave. Mandibles (
<figureCitation box="[1037,1167,263,287]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figures 2B</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[211,243,295,319]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">3B</figureCitation>
) with lateral longitudinal ridge occupying less than two-thirds of apical region; external margin strongly developed, attenuated anteriorly. Left mandible (
<figureCitation box="[1048,1163,327,351]" captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetId="figure-6@6.[145,1102,167,1045]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Figure 3. Left and right mandible, dorsal view. (A) Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 3B</figureCitation>
) with first dorsal tooth developed, sinuate and bifurcate, accessory tooth near lateral longitudinal ridge; second dorsal tooth little developed and resembling a small hill; first ventral tooth with tooth accessory, third ventral tooth consisting of two structures with the bases fused. Submentum with setae arranged in row on anterolateral margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[211,1172,550,829]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,301,550,574]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Thorax.</emphasis>
Pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[440,556,550,574]" captionStart="Figure 2" captionStartId="5.[211,278,1629,1651]" captionTargetBox="[238,1145,161,1595]" captionTargetId="figure-5@5.[238,1145,161,1596]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="Figure 2. Head and protorax of Leptochirus (Tropiochirus). (A) L. (T.) helleri; (B) L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype; (C) L. (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype; (D) L. (T.) milton sp. nov. holotype; (E) L. (T.) pachoensis; (F) L. (T.) proteus; (G) L. (T.) venezuelanus; (H) L. (T.) yunganus; (I) L. (T.) zischkaianus. Scale bars = 1.0 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 2B</figureCitation>
) a little wider than long (PL: 2.2, PW: 2.50); superior marginal line of hypomeron not interrupted, not bent to dorsal region at anterior margin and almost reaching posterior margin; without pair of small depressions near basal constriction. Inferior marginal line of hypomeron reaching anterior margin. Apex of prosternal process strongly expanded and resembling a circular plate, extending considerably beyond the lateral process of hypomeron. Metaventrite with sparse fine punctures in middle region and without small longitudinal median depression near posterior edge. Mesoscutellum with apex rounded. Elytra longer than broad and with pair of small depressions on posterolateral edge (EL: 2.85, EW: 2.44).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[211,1172,869,988]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[211,322,869,893]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Cylindrical. Sternite III with keel of apex rounded. Tergite IX (
<figureCitation box="[1053,1163,869,893]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 4J</figureCitation>
) sclerotized with left and right plates separated, each with five or six setae of various length. Tergite X (
<figureCitation box="[413,520,932,956]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 4J</figureCitation>
) membraneous except for sclerotized apical part, with two pairs of long apical setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[211,1172,1028,1243]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">
<emphasis box="[211,276,1028,1052]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Male.</emphasis>
Sternite IX (
<figureCitation box="[425,545,1028,1052]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 4K</figureCitation>
) composed of two plates, distal plate sclerotized except for membranous apex, anterior margin rounded, posterior margin sinuate and with two long setae; proximal plate less sclerotized, greater than apical, broadened in middle and with a projecting angle at posterior border. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[874,1016,1124,1148]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 4G–I</figureCitation>
) with median lobe slightly bulbous at base, rounded at apex, weakly sclerotized on dorsal side and a small plate sclerotized on ventral side that is joined with the sclerotized region on dorsal side; parameres short, pointed and fused dorsally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[211,1172,1283,1371]" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">
<emphasis box="[211,297,1283,1307]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Female.</emphasis>
Similar to male, except for the gonocoxites divided longitudinally (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1160,1283,1307]" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="6.[143,210,1458,1480]" captionText="Figure 4. Leptochirus (Tropiochirus) helleri. (A) Aedeagus left lateral view; (B) aedeagus dorsal view; (C) aedeagus right lateral view; (D) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (E) sternite IX of male; (F) right gonocoxites of female. L. (T.) marina sp. nov. holotype: (G) aedeagus left lateral view; (H) aedeagus dorsal view; (I) aedeagus right lateral view; (J) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (K) sternite IX of male; (L) right gonocoxites of female. Leptochirus (T.) mery sp. nov. holotype. (M) Aedeagus left lateral view; (N) aedeagus dorsal view; (O) aedeagus right lateral view; (P) tergum X [T10] and tergite IX [T9] of male; (Q) sternite IX of male; (R) right gonocoxites of female. Scale bars = 0.25 mm." pageId="11" pageNumber="1267">Figure 4L</figureCitation>
). The distal plate with apex membranous and long seta; proximal plate with the posterior region pointed.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
